    <section id="house-skin" class="Work">
      <h3 class="Work_heading">The House of Skin and Ash</h3>
      <p>A gothic young adult fiction that arose from my Master’s thesis looking at the abjection of sisterhood in gothic YA texts. Not having a sister myself I probably find sisterhood in itself abject and a perfect topic for a gothic story.</p>
      <p>Ghosts Sylvie and Claire steal bodies of other girls so they can live again. But the girls struggle to rebuild their life in Melbourne and Sylvie knows she has to stop Claire from stealing more bodies before their past catches up with them.</p>
      <p>However, Sylvie isn’t prepared to give back the body she took, especially after she falls for her host’s ex-girlfriend.</p>
      <p>The story is about not belonging in your own skin and imposter syndrome; the St Aubert sisters certainly do not belong.</p>
      <p>The initial inspiration was the music video Gallows by CocoRosie and my desire to explore Australian Gothic.</p>
      <p>The audience is fifteen-plus girls who like read about complex female relationships, gothic and LGBT themes. Comparable Australian titles are Black Spring by Alison Croggon, Fairytales for Wilde Girls by Allyse Near and books by Margo Lanagan.</p>
      <p>It was inspired in part by the video clip ‘Gallows’ by the group CocoRosie, directed by the wonderful Emma Freeman.</p>
